  "prompt": "Can pigs show affection?",
  "response": "Yes, pigs can show affection. They are social animals and can form strong bonds with both humans and other animals. Pigs demonstrate their affection in various ways, such as through gentle nudging, following people around, or leaning against them. They may also enjoy being petted and can respond positively to human touch and voice. Additionally, pigs are known to communicate with a range of vocalizations and body language to express their feelings, including affection.",
